You've come to the right place.

262
00:22:22,232 --> 00:22:26,099
How about turtle soup? We make good turtle soup.

263
00:22:26,099 --> 00:22:31,513
No, you know what I mean. Something that really works.

264
00:22:31,513 --> 00:22:33,401
Like…

265
00:22:35,328 --> 00:22:38,355
Snake, you know?

266
00:22:50,135 --> 00:22:52,735
- Are you sure that's the one?
- Yup.

267
00:22:52,735 --> 00:22:55,599
If it disappeared near Bam Valley, it must be around here.

268
00:22:55,599 --> 00:23:00,484
And I heard that store is making bank (getting rich) lately. I'm sure that's the one.

269
00:23:00,484 --> 00:23:02,606
I don't know about this.

270
00:23:02,606 --> 00:23:07,040
If it's within 700 meters, the tracker should go off. But there's no signal.

271
00:23:07,040 --> 00:23:11,219
You just wait. We've planted the seed, they'll make a move soon.

272
00:23:12,132 --> 00:23:15,327
I heard you study mushrooms there, too.

273
00:23:15,327 --> 00:23:20,123
Do you study Common Rustgill, too?

274
00:23:20,123 --> 00:23:24,399
It's a dangerous mushroom. Of course, we do.

275
00:23:24,399 --> 00:23:28,570
Can a regular person… extract poison from it?

276
00:23:28,570 --> 00:23:33,491
I doubt it. You'd need proper tools to do it.

277
00:23:33,491 --> 00:23:36,473
Why do you ask about the mushroom?

278
00:23:36,473 --> 00:23:42,373
This is his guess, but someone's putting the poison in yogurt to kill people.

279
00:23:42,373 --> 00:23:44,137
Seriously? Who? Why? Why?

280
00:23:44,137 --> 00:23:46,191
I said it's his guess.

281
00:23:46,191 --> 00:23:48,401
Do you think that's possible?

282
00:23:48,401 --> 00:23:51,905
It's not impossible.

283
00:23:51,905 --> 00:23:55,200
Someone who knows an extraction method

284
00:23:55,200 --> 00:23:59,315
and the geography or vegetation of Jirisan could do it.

285
00:23:59,315 --> 00:24:02,207
But that would only be the rangers.

286
00:24:02,207 --> 00:24:07,525
Why would a park ranger… do such a thing?

287
00:24:09,648 --> 00:24:12,214
Hold on. Look! Look over there!

288
00:24:14,652 --> 00:24:15,954
Hey.

289
00:24:15,954 --> 00:24:17,163
Please take this.

290
00:24:17,164 --> 00:24:18,490
- Yes.
- Hide, hide now.

291
00:24:18,490 --> 00:24:22,507
- Quick! Quick! Follow them!
- Seat belts! Get the belts on.

292
00:24:53,758 --> 00:24:57,253
You're too close. They'll find out.

293
00:25:02,267 --> 00:25:05,117
Oh! We're getting a signal!

294
00:25:39,971 --> 00:25:43,141
- Why aren't they coming out?
[Gangwon Restoration]

295
00:25:43,141 --> 00:25:45,010
Should we go in?

296
00:25:45,010 --> 00:25:49,219
Wait. Wait. Should we call the police first?

297
00:25:49,219 --> 00:25:51,266
Yi Kang.

298
00:25:57,781 --> 00:26:00,015
Freeze!

299
00:26:00,700 --> 00:26:02,501
Senior!

300
00:26:25,700 --> 00:26:30,051
Who the hell do you think you are? Do you own that mountain?

301
00:26:30,051 --> 00:26:34,526
Don't you know the law regarding wild animal protection?

302
00:26:34,526 --> 00:26:36,178
Look!

303
00:26:36,178 --> 00:26:40,849
If you process, distribute, or store wild animals in danger of extinction,

304
00:26:40,849 --> 00:26:45,453
you'll be imprisoned for 2 years or charged with a fine of 20,000,000 won (US $18,000).

305
00:26:45,453 --> 00:26:47,872
You are blabbering about something you know nothing about, kid.

306
00:26:47,900 --> 00:26:53,400
My family's been collecting herbs and catching animals on that mountain since my grandfather's grandfather.

307
00:26:55,021 --> 00:26:56,723
You must be real proud.

308
00:26:56,723 --> 00:27:00,176
What? Come here! Come here!

309
00:27:00,176 --> 00:27:03,190
I'm here! I'm here. I'm here. What are you going to do?

310
00:27:03,190 --> 00:27:05,680
What? Why?

311
00:27:05,682 --> 00:27:10,666
National Park? My butt! Humans came before the mountains!

312
00:27:10,666 --> 00:27:14,846
Is that why you caught so many snakes? Why don't you wipe out the entire species!

313
00:27:14,846 --> 00:27:17,577
You look like a snake!

314
00:27:17,577 --> 00:27:21,489
What have those poor snakes ever done to you?

315
00:27:21,489 --> 00:27:23,740
I should have known when you winked at me.

316
00:27:23,740 --> 00:27:25,040
Stop him, not me.

317
00:27:25,040 --> 00:27:27,980
It's just useless snakes, what's the matter with that?

318
00:27:27,980 --> 00:27:29,910
Why?

319
00:27:29,914 --> 00:27:32,157
Get off of me!

320
00:27:44,053 --> 00:27:45,989
Is that the newbie?

321
00:27:45,989 --> 00:27:47,748
Yup.

322
00:27:48,625 --> 00:27:52,729
He's tall but very plain-looking.

323
00:27:52,729 --> 00:27:57,238
I wouldn't say he is plain. He's not normal, though.

324
00:27:58,485 --> 00:28:00,911
Is that so?

325
00:28:01,863 --> 00:28:04,740
What a shame for such a young man.

326
00:28:12,707 --> 00:28:15,543
23 black and 18 yellow rat snakes,

327
00:28:15,543 --> 00:28:19,571
and 53 tiger keelbacks. That's 94 in total.

328
00:28:22,050 --> 00:28:24,150
Well done.

329
00:28:24,976 --> 00:28:26,679
Thanks a lot.

330
00:28:27,847 --> 00:28:29,347
Good night.

331
00:28:30,199 --> 00:28:32,134
Oh, right.

332
00:28:34,329 --> 00:28:36,288
We should head back now.

333
00:28:37,023 --> 00:28:38,624
Yes.

334
00:29:40,003 --> 00:29:44,424
This trail is a lot worse than other restricted areas.

335
00:29:44,424 --> 00:29:46,426
Not even herb collectors come here.

336
00:29:46,426 --> 00:29:50,045
And since there are no humans, it's an animal paradise.

337
00:30:03,259 --> 00:30:09,694
And… this is the only graveyard where you can see Cheonwangbong Peak.

338
00:30:30,370 --> 00:30:32,664
Is this it?

339
00:30:32,664 --> 00:30:35,324
Yes. This is the place.

340
00:30:57,121 --> 00:30:59,223
Nothing, right?

341
00:31:00,850 --> 00:31:03,795
Yeah… there is nothing.

342
00:31:03,795 --> 00:31:05,755
Let's go down.

343
00:31:05,755 --> 00:31:07,740
We've got a special patrol to do.

344
00:31:14,747 --> 00:31:17,725
How come you came with me without a question?

345
00:31:17,725 --> 00:31:20,687
You always yell at me for saying nonsense.

346
00:31:20,687 --> 00:31:23,022
But today you came without a complaint.

347
00:31:23,022 --> 00:31:25,508
It's weird, you're Demon Seo.

348
00:31:25,508 --> 00:31:28,469
You don't want to live long, huh?

349
00:31:41,224 --> 00:31:45,128
Dammit. Who do they think they are?

350
00:31:45,128 --> 00:31:47,505
Hurry up before it gets dark.

351
00:31:47,505 --> 00:31:50,324
What if we get caught again?

352
00:31:50,325 --> 00:31:52,135
How else will we pay the fine?

353
00:31:52,135 --> 00:31:54,345
Are we going to starve the kids?

354
00:31:54,345 --> 00:31:57,105
It's either do or die.

355
00:32:00,793 --> 00:32:01,711
What are you doing?

356
00:32:01,712 --> 00:32:03,862
You go that way.

357
00:32:25,818 --> 00:32:28,813
How could such a graveyard still remain in a national park?

358
00:32:28,813 --> 00:32:31,816
Aren't illegal properties subject to demolition here?

359
00:32:31,816 --> 00:32:34,493
For the graves that were here before it became a national park,

360
00:32:34,494 --> 00:32:37,054
families often don't agree to move them.

361
00:32:37,054 --> 00:32:39,182
Like that one.

362
00:32:39,182 --> 00:32:43,244
Chuseok (Korean Thanksgiving) is over, and the Cold Food festival's not here yet.

363
00:32:43,244 --> 00:32:46,213
No one will come for a while, which means no injuries.

364
00:32:46,214 --> 00:32:48,006
Not only families come here.

365
00:32:48,007 --> 00:32:50,926
There are many animals around gravesites, too.

366
00:32:50,927 --> 00:32:55,807
Especially, snakes are spotted a lot under a stone table.

367
00:33:43,646 --> 00:33:46,249
Haedong One, 3km from Saema Valley. An explosion was heard!!

368
00:33:46,249 --> 00:33:48,250
Check for an SOS call!

369
00:34:28,916 --> 00:34:30,067
Don't come up, Senior.

370
00:34:30,068 --> 00:34:32,094
Stay there!

371
00:35:16,464 --> 00:35:18,591
A potato bomb?

372
00:35:18,591 --> 00:35:19,717
That's right.

373
00:35:19,717 --> 00:35:25,181
Homemade bombs were used by poachers who hunted Asian black bears in the sixties and seventies.

374
00:35:25,181 --> 00:35:29,251
Bear livers and gallbladders had enormous monetary value back then.

375
00:35:29,252 --> 00:35:32,462
So the poachers set them up here and there on Jirisan.

376
00:35:32,463 --> 00:35:36,050
Kind of like a landmine.

377
00:35:36,050 --> 00:35:38,176
But they're still on the mountain?

378
00:35:38,177 --> 00:35:40,595
In the sixties, when the national park was established,

379
00:35:40,596 --> 00:35:42,764
everyone, including the villagers, searched

380
00:35:42,765 --> 00:35:44,724
and removed the remaining bombs.

381
00:35:44,725 --> 00:35:47,928
But they couldn't reach the deep restricted trails.

382
00:35:49,263 --> 00:35:50,856
This is Jirisan, after all.

383
00:35:50,857 --> 00:35:54,085
But how did this old junk explode?

384
00:35:54,085 --> 00:35:56,987
The casing of a potato bomb is entirely sealed with wax.

385
00:35:56,988 --> 00:35:58,655
And because no wind or rain could get in,

386
00:35:58,656 --> 00:36:01,750
the detonator and explosive must have remained inside.

387
00:36:03,235 --> 00:36:07,097
We keep telling them not to enter that area but they do.

388
00:36:11,560 --> 00:36:13,762
I have something to tell you.

389
00:36:15,214 --> 00:36:19,418
We patrolled the site before the explosion.

390
00:36:20,903 --> 00:36:25,599
We've looked all around for any dangerous objects.

391
00:36:25,600 --> 00:36:29,762
But the bomb wasn't there at that time.

392
00:36:29,762 --> 00:36:31,063
Is that true?

393
00:36:34,458 --> 00:36:35,626
Yes.

394
00:36:35,626 --> 00:36:37,211
Did you really look everywhere?

395
00:36:37,211 --> 00:36:39,529
Maybe you confused it with grass or branch or something?

396
00:36:39,530 --> 00:36:41,156
No.

397
00:36:41,157 --> 00:36:43,134
There really was nothing then.

398
00:36:43,134 --> 00:36:45,011
I'm positive.

399
00:36:45,011 --> 00:36:47,321
Are you positively sure?

400
00:36:50,599 --> 00:36:53,202
If you're not sure, this is a huge problem.

401
00:36:53,202 --> 00:36:57,405
It means a civilian died because of a park ranger's mistake.

402
00:37:05,170 --> 00:37:06,680
[Gangwon Restoration]

403
00:37:13,481 --> 00:37:18,176
Take your mother with you... Take your mother with you.

404
00:37:18,950 --> 00:37:21,797
I can't live alone, my son.

405
00:37:21,797 --> 00:37:25,384
What the hell is wrong with you all?

406
00:37:25,384 --> 00:37:29,096
You act like you own the mountain,

407
00:37:29,096 --> 00:37:33,291
and look what you've done to my husband!

408
00:37:36,912 --> 00:37:41,454
- Please calm down, and let's…
- How can you say that? My husband died before my eyes!

409
00:37:41,454 --> 00:37:44,484
Bring him back. Bring him back!

410
00:37:44,484 --> 00:37:46,681
Bring my husband back!

411
00:37:46,681 --> 00:37:52,103
About the accident that happened to your husband, our hearts go out to you at this time.

412
00:37:52,103 --> 00:37:53,687
Accident?

413
00:37:53,688 --> 00:37:55,814
Did you say an accident?

414
00:37:55,815 --> 00:38:02,232
I saw… those two on the mountain that day.

415
00:38:02,232 --> 00:38:05,055
What did they do while they were up there?

416
00:38:05,055 --> 00:38:09,370
What did they do until the bomb exploded?!

417
00:38:10,429 --> 00:38:13,632
The reason he went to the mountain that day...

418
00:38:14,792 --> 00:38:17,144
is because of you all...

419
00:38:17,144 --> 00:38:22,958
He needed to make money somehow after getting all the snakes taken!

420
00:38:22,958 --> 00:38:25,052
You've…

421
00:38:27,296 --> 00:38:30,057
Murdered my husband!

422
00:38:34,186 --> 00:38:39,415
I can't let him go like this!

423
00:38:40,943 --> 00:38:42,152
Are you okay?

424
00:38:42,153 --> 00:38:46,699
I won't move a step until you pay for his life!

425
00:38:46,699 --> 00:38:51,745
I'll stay here with my husband!

426
00:38:51,746 --> 00:38:54,131
Calm down.

427
00:38:56,660 --> 00:38:57,990
Poor thing...

428
00:38:57,990 --> 00:39:00,496
What do I do now?

429
00:39:00,496 --> 00:39:04,349
Bring him back!

430
00:39:06,200 --> 00:39:08,070
What do I do now?

431
00:39:26,420 --> 00:39:31,790
[Gangwon Restoration]

432
00:39:35,260 --> 00:39:40,140
[Jirisan National Park Administration]

433
00:39:45,370 --> 00:39:46,720
[Who's responsible for the coffin that cannot depart?]

434
00:39:46,720 --> 00:39:49,540
[Neglect by the National Park Administration costs human resource]

435
00:39:51,222 --> 00:39:53,723
He's been like that for days, already.

436
00:39:53,724 --> 00:39:55,475
We must come up with measures.

437
00:39:55,476 --> 00:39:56,351
That's right.

438
00:39:56,352 --> 00:39:58,770
It's still hot during the day.

439
00:39:58,771 --> 00:40:03,108
If the corpse starts to rot, the media will get even worse.

440
00:40:03,109 --> 00:40:07,779
Why don't we compensate them now?

441
00:40:08,547 --> 00:40:10,949
We cannot.

442
00:40:10,949 --> 00:40:13,326
What happened is unfortunate,

443
00:40:13,327 --> 00:40:16,597
but it happened in a restricted area.

444
00:40:16,597 --> 00:40:18,265
If we compensate them,

445
00:40:18,265 --> 00:40:22,961
the grounds for regulating illegal hikers will be weakened.

446
00:40:22,962 --> 00:40:24,796
But we can't leave them like that, can we?

447
00:40:24,797 --> 00:40:27,708
We must take responsibility somehow.

448
00:40:28,634 --> 00:40:30,769
That is right.

449
00:40:32,805 --> 00:40:34,757
Someone…

450
00:40:35,641 --> 00:40:37,901
must take responsibility.

451
00:40:39,019 --> 00:40:40,487
Seo Yi Kang.

452
00:40:40,487 --> 00:40:43,356
Is it true that you were there before the accident?

453
00:40:43,357 --> 00:40:48,027
You could've recognized and removed such a dangerous thing.

454
00:40:48,028 --> 00:40:51,172
What's wrong with Haedong Station lately?

455
00:40:51,172 --> 00:40:54,018
Hey, have you seen a potato bomb?

456
00:40:54,018 --> 00:40:58,037
How can you remove something you've never seen?

457
00:40:58,038 --> 00:40:59,747
That's not all.

458
00:40:59,748 --> 00:41:03,886
Last time with Granny Geum Rye, too. Why are there so many accidents?

459
00:41:08,215 --> 00:41:11,301
I'll say this as a team leader.

460
00:41:11,302 --> 00:41:12,802
Stay vigilant.

461
00:41:12,803 --> 00:41:15,221
That stupid team leader, this team leader, that crap…

462
00:41:15,222 --> 00:41:18,366
You should have become a team leader then.

463
00:41:27,276 --> 00:41:29,152
How did it go?

464
00:41:29,153 --> 00:41:31,463
What did the chief say?

465
00:41:31,463 --> 00:41:36,359
He'll take responsibility for everything and resign.

466
00:41:44,835 --> 00:41:46,728
Captain!

467
00:41:47,421 --> 00:41:48,880
What Hyun Jo said was the truth.

468
00:41:48,881 --> 00:41:52,467
There was nothing at the gravesite when we were on patrol.

469
00:41:52,468 --> 00:41:55,220
Someone placed it there after our patrol.

470
00:41:55,221 --> 00:41:59,088
If we find the person, we'll prove that it wasn't our fault.

471
00:41:59,088 --> 00:41:59,975
All right.

472
00:41:59,976 --> 00:42:03,595
Let's say that someone did like you said.

473
00:42:03,595 --> 00:42:07,166
Then finding that person is the police's job.

474
00:42:07,166 --> 00:42:08,375
But…

475
00:42:08,375 --> 00:42:11,035
We have our own job.

476
00:42:11,035 --> 00:42:13,663
It's to protect those who come to the mountain.

477
00:42:15,783 --> 00:42:19,069
Local residents are the ones who come here the most.

478
00:42:19,069 --> 00:42:21,704
Our priority…

479
00:42:21,705 --> 00:42:23,899
is to regain their trust.

480
00:42:26,085 --> 00:42:27,845
See you later.

481
00:42:59,343 --> 00:43:01,619
Bring him...

482
00:43:01,619 --> 00:43:04,239
Bring him back!

483
00:43:08,210 --> 00:43:10,962
Bring my husband back.

484
00:43:11,647 --> 00:43:14,407
Please bring my husband back...

485
00:43:16,151 --> 00:43:18,636
Bring him back.

486
00:43:19,346 --> 00:43:21,907
How am I going to live without him?

487
00:43:23,267 --> 00:43:25,960
Bring him back!

488
00:43:31,860 --> 00:43:35,680
[Jirisan National Park Administration]

489
00:43:43,704 --> 00:43:46,248
My poor son...

490
00:43:59,386 --> 00:44:01,755
Dad.

491
00:44:02,556 --> 00:44:04,783
Dad!

492
00:44:06,560 --> 00:44:08,850
Dad.

493
00:44:10,780 --> 00:44:12,830
Dad.

494
00:44:19,022 --> 00:44:21,116
Let's go back.

495
00:44:23,427 --> 00:44:26,287
I can't let it end like this.

496
00:44:27,014 --> 00:44:29,099
Don't make matters worse.

497
00:44:29,099 --> 00:44:32,677
Chief resigned, trying so hard to settle this down.

498
00:44:34,546 --> 00:44:36,831
I saw a hand.

499
00:44:37,691 --> 00:44:43,334
There were five scratch scars from a small animal's claws.

500
00:44:43,334 --> 00:44:45,323
I can never…

501
00:44:45,991 --> 00:44:48,126
forget that hand.

502
00:44:49,144 --> 00:44:50,979
Enough.

503
00:44:54,525 --> 00:44:56,584
On that day,

504
00:44:57,403 --> 00:45:01,489
someone else was on that mountain other than the victim.

505
00:45:03,984 --> 00:45:06,128
I will find that person,

506
00:45:07,329 --> 00:45:09,556
no matter what it takes.

507
00:45:31,050 --> 00:45:35,050
[If you find dangerous materials, please do not touch but report immediately to the National Park Administration Office]

508
00:45:35,050 --> 00:45:38,550
[Notice: Beware of dangerous material]

509
00:45:42,910 --> 00:45:45,470
[Notice: Beware of dangerous material]

510
00:46:03,802 --> 00:46:05,770
Who's there?

511
00:46:19,568 --> 00:46:21,420
What brings you here?

512
00:46:21,420 --> 00:46:23,964
I have something to ask you.

513
00:46:23,964 --> 00:46:27,992
Okay. I'll be done in a second, I'll be done shortly.

514
00:46:30,412 --> 00:46:33,306
These were all found on Jirisan.

515
00:46:33,306 --> 00:46:35,609
You know, to capture wild animals

516
00:46:35,609 --> 00:46:38,695
like bears, raccoons, snakes, and badgers.

517
00:46:38,695 --> 00:46:41,422
Although this time, a person was sacrificed…

518
00:46:47,080 --> 00:46:51,730
[Campaign to notify and inform of dangerous material]

519
00:46:52,476 --> 00:46:54,827
We are busy enough with looking after the shelters.

520
00:46:54,827 --> 00:46:58,548
Why did the newbie have to be sick today?

521
00:46:58,548 --> 00:47:00,392
That's strange now that I think of it.

522
00:47:00,392 --> 00:47:02,151
Where did this sick kid go this early morning?

523
00:47:02,152 --> 00:47:03,420
He wasn't in the residence.

524
00:47:03,420 --> 00:47:04,320
No?

525
00:47:04,321 --> 00:47:06,130
He must be really sick.

526
00:47:06,130 --> 00:47:09,951
He called me early, saying he'd get checked at a big hospital.

527
00:47:09,952 --> 00:47:11,536
Huh?

528
00:47:11,537 --> 00:47:12,703
Really?

529
00:47:12,704 --> 00:47:14,697
What's wrong with him?

530
00:47:17,167 --> 00:47:19,235
His head.

531
00:47:19,235 --> 00:47:21,095
Head?

532
00:47:26,218 --> 00:47:27,510
Head?

533
00:47:27,511 --> 00:47:28,904
Hey.

534
00:47:28,904 --> 00:47:31,973
We don't have enough drinks. Someone needs to go get some more.

535
00:47:31,973 --> 00:47:33,034
Okay.

536
00:47:33,034 --> 00:47:34,684
No, no. I'll go. I'll go.

537
00:47:34,685 --> 00:47:36,185
Can you help me, Yang Sun?

538
00:47:36,186 --> 00:47:37,180
Please come with me.

539
00:47:37,180 --> 00:47:39,480
Why's everyone so awkward today?

540
00:47:39,481 --> 00:47:41,732
No, just hurry.

541
00:47:42,984 --> 00:47:44,402
Why are they going together?

542
00:47:44,403 --> 00:47:46,354
The potato bomb?

543
00:47:46,354 --> 00:47:47,572
Yes.

544
00:47:47,573 --> 00:47:52,293
I heard that you've been researching them.

545
00:47:52,293 --> 00:47:53,953
Was it…

546
00:47:53,953 --> 00:47:58,174
really one of the bombs the poachers used in the sixties?

547
00:47:58,174 --> 00:48:04,009
Is it possible someone copied one from the past?

548
00:48:04,009 --> 00:48:05,507
No.

549
00:48:05,507 --> 00:48:08,777
You can't get any parts of the bomb from anywhere now.

550
00:48:08,777 --> 00:48:12,839
I'm certain it was what the poachers used in the past.

551
00:48:18,812 --> 00:48:20,563
You said…

552
00:48:20,564 --> 00:48:23,816
they removed a bunch of potato bombs from the mountains.

553
00:48:23,817 --> 00:48:27,787
Were the bombs sent anywhere?

554
00:48:28,563 --> 00:48:31,949
Like a museum or a national park...

555
00:48:31,950 --> 00:48:35,570
Why would a park keep such a dangerous thing?

556
00:48:35,570 --> 00:48:39,365
They were dismantled and burned immediately.

557
00:48:40,775 --> 00:48:42,143
I see…

558
00:48:42,143 --> 00:48:46,639
Why do you ask?

559
00:48:46,639 --> 00:48:50,076
Do you think it wasn't an accident?

560
00:48:53,096 --> 00:48:54,472
Yes.

561
00:48:54,473 --> 00:48:57,141
The possibility of that is very low.

562
00:48:57,142 --> 00:48:59,727
I mean, there were some people in the town

563
00:48:59,728 --> 00:49:03,814
who found them on their own and kept them privately,

564
00:49:03,815 --> 00:49:07,568
but I heard they were all confiscated.

565
00:49:07,568 --> 00:49:09,904
Privately owned bombs?

566
00:49:09,905 --> 00:49:11,531
By whom?

567
00:49:11,531 --> 00:49:16,419
Some of the workers kept them as souvenirs.

568
00:49:16,419 --> 00:49:20,264
Could I get their list of them?

569
00:49:20,264 --> 00:49:23,359
I told you.

570
00:49:23,359 --> 00:49:25,711
It's extremely unlikely.

571
00:49:25,712 --> 00:49:27,822
That's okay.

572
00:49:33,011 --> 00:49:35,197
We don't have a list,

573
00:49:35,197 --> 00:49:39,634
but I can introduce you to one of the workers from then.

574
00:49:39,634 --> 00:49:46,065
He'll probably know other workers.

575
00:50:10,007 --> 00:50:11,952
- I'll take this, too.
- No, it's fine.

576
00:50:11,952 --> 00:50:15,462
I've been working out, so my arms feel strong.

577
00:50:15,462 --> 00:50:18,556
Boy, these are light as a feather!

578
00:50:21,309 --> 00:50:24,220
Oh, this is the heavy one!

579
00:50:29,234 --> 00:50:33,020
You must be tired because of all this.

580
00:50:33,020 --> 00:50:35,565
That stupid potato bomb or sweet potato bomb…

581
00:50:35,565 --> 00:50:37,533
Who's there?

582
00:50:39,536 --> 00:50:42,455
...how did they get left behind on the mountain?

583
00:50:49,463 --> 00:50:51,889
Don't worry, though.

584
00:50:51,889 --> 00:50:54,267
It won't happen again.

585
00:50:54,267 --> 00:50:56,786
This is when you need a change of surroundings.

586
00:50:56,786 --> 00:51:00,181
Do you want to go for a drive on your next day off?
[Dangerous material]

587
00:51:00,182 --> 00:51:02,784
There's this Milking Goats Festival.
[Please contact the office]

588
00:51:02,784 --> 00:51:05,044
It's supposed to be really fun.

589
00:51:05,854 --> 00:51:10,575
Would you like to go milk some goats with me?

590
00:51:11,818 --> 00:51:15,196
I'm sorry, but I need to go to the station right now.

591
00:51:15,197 --> 00:51:17,097
I'm sorry.

592
00:51:18,283 --> 00:51:20,259
Okay.

593
00:51:25,791 --> 00:51:27,850
Dang, not again.

594
00:51:28,977 --> 00:51:31,354
What on earth is the problem?

595
00:52:07,332 --> 00:52:09,409
Hello?

596
00:52:11,503 --> 00:52:13,905
Anyone there?

597
00:52:21,054 --> 00:52:22,380
Who is it?

598
00:52:22,380 --> 00:52:26,181
Hello. I'm from the national park.

599
00:52:26,181 --> 00:52:28,018
The national park?

600
00:52:28,019 --> 00:52:31,272
Mr. Kang at the Restoration Center referred me here.

601
00:52:31,273 --> 00:52:35,025
I heard you were a part of the bomb removal process on Jirisan.

602
00:52:35,026 --> 00:52:36,610
Yes, I was. So?

603
00:52:36,611 --> 00:52:41,223
I have something to ask about the potato bombs.

604
00:52:50,892 --> 00:52:53,502
I don't know anything.

605
00:52:53,503 --> 00:52:55,246
One second!

606
00:52:55,246 --> 00:52:57,248
I know you've got nothing to do with the latest accident.

607
00:52:57,248 --> 00:53:00,743
I'm only asking to check something.

608
00:53:00,743 --> 00:53:04,138
Is there anything that you know about the recent bomb incident?

609
00:53:04,139 --> 00:53:06,974
I told you I know nothing!

610
00:53:06,974 --> 00:53:10,744
The bomb just disappeared!

611
00:53:10,744 --> 00:53:13,272
The bomb disappeared?

612
00:53:15,083 --> 00:53:17,568
I swear I left it in here.

613
00:53:17,569 --> 00:53:20,779
But it just disappeared without a trace.

614
00:53:20,780 --> 00:53:24,708
I didn't say anything because I didn't want people to get the wrong idea.

615
00:53:24,708 --> 00:53:27,378
So pretend you didn't see this.

616
00:53:27,378 --> 00:53:30,373
I don't want to get my granddaughter in trouble.

617
00:53:31,499 --> 00:53:33,709
Your granddaughter?

618
00:53:35,578 --> 00:53:36,730
Hello.

619
00:53:36,730 --> 00:53:38,189
Where are the people?

620
00:53:38,189 --> 00:53:40,950
They should be here soon...

621
00:53:40,950 --> 00:53:42,985
Oh, Grandma's here.

622
00:53:42,985 --> 00:53:45,012
Hello!

623
00:53:46,806 --> 00:53:48,550
It's been a while.

624
00:53:48,550 --> 00:53:50,551
Welcome.

625
00:53:55,139 --> 00:53:58,942
Girl, you haven't called in days!

626
00:53:58,942 --> 00:54:00,653
Have you been skipping your meals?

627
00:54:00,654 --> 00:54:04,865
It's not just me. We've all been busy.

628
00:54:05,659 --> 00:54:07,818
Are you okay?

629
00:54:10,455 --> 00:54:12,373
Did you come alone?

630
00:54:12,374 --> 00:54:13,692
What about the others?

631
00:54:13,692 --> 00:54:15,918
They said they'd all come…

632
00:54:15,919 --> 00:54:18,788
Oh, there they are.

633
00:54:25,553 --> 00:54:27,221
Thank you for coming.

634
00:54:27,222 --> 00:54:29,366
I'm not here to forgive you.

635
00:54:29,366 --> 00:54:32,510
I want to watch what you all have to say.

636
00:54:35,279 --> 00:54:39,900
Let's go in first.

637
00:54:39,900 --> 00:54:42,945
All of you, let's go inside.

638
00:55:18,570 --> 00:55:21,310
[Community Hall]

639
00:56:12,494 --> 00:56:18,636
If her work finds out about this, she might get in trouble.

640
00:56:18,636 --> 00:56:20,768
You're her colleague.

641
00:56:20,768 --> 00:56:25,147
So please just let it pass.

642
00:56:51,574 --> 00:56:53,992
I saw a hand.

643
00:56:55,595 --> 00:56:58,655
There were five scratch scars....

644
00:56:58,655 --> 00:57:01,750
from a small animal's claws.

645
00:57:44,360 --> 00:57:48,630
♫ I’m falling, I’m falling ♫

646
00:57:48,630 --> 00:57:53,660
♫ between the gaps in time ♫

647
00:57:53,660 --> 00:58:02,690
♫ I’m broken like a dying star ♫

648
00:58:02,690 --> 00:58:06,810
♫ I lost you, l lost you ♫

649
00:58:06,810 --> 00:58:12,020
♫ Are you lost again? ♫

650
00:58:12,020 --> 00:58:15,330
♫ I’m falling again ♫

651
00:58:15,330 --> 00:58:19,150
♫ endlessly falling ♫

652
00:58:28,540 --> 00:58:31,730
[Jirisan]

653
00:58:31,730 --> 00:58:34,801
Three bombs went missing. There's still one left.

654
00:58:34,802 --> 00:58:36,903
That kid might know something.

655
00:58:36,903 --> 00:58:39,682
Senior Yang Sun's cousin, huh?

656
00:58:39,682 --> 00:58:40,766
It's that person.

657
00:58:40,767 --> 00:58:41,725
Where's Yang Sun?

658
00:58:41,726 --> 00:58:43,844
Yang Sun!

659
00:58:43,844 --> 00:58:45,687
If I had believed you from the beginning...

660
00:58:45,688 --> 00:58:47,272
could we have saved her?

661
00:58:47,273 --> 00:58:49,316
[Someone noticed our plan.]

662
00:58:49,317 --> 00:58:51,401
It was one of the rangers.

663
00:58:51,402 --> 00:58:53,320
You're the only one I can trust.
[Kang Hyun Jo]

664
00:58:53,321 --> 00:58:54,988
Can you help me?

665
00:58:54,989 --> 00:58:58,920
I can prove that he's the criminal.

666
00:58:58,920 --> 00:59:01,470
♫ I lost you ♫

667
00:59:01,470 --> 00:59:06,020
♫ even I lost myself ♫

668
00:59:06,020 --> 00:59:07,750
♫ I’m falling ♫
